oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Cumberland Mountain School
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Four views of buildings at Cumberland Mountain School, including the manual training shop, Gray Hall, the girls' dormitory, Dorton Hall, the boys' dormitory, and the interior of the student library. The original Cumberland Mountain School opened in 1919 and closed in 1938. It then served as the location for Cumberland County's Upper Cumberland Human Resource Agency office and home to the Youth Impact Center for boys.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
